00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:58.000
One of the remaining questions we had was,

00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:03.000
what is your favorite thing about working with Databricks?

00:17:03.000 --> 00:17:06.000
Oh, honestly,

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:09.000
what I really like is how complete the ecosystem is

00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:12.000
and how easy it is to use.

00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:15.000
Like I think in terms of like peak AWS, right?

00:17:15.000 --> 00:17:17.000
Whenever you would need a Spark cluster,

00:17:17.000 --> 00:17:20.000
you would have to have an entire Hadoop cluster implementation

00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:21.000
with Spark on top,

00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:23.000
which means an EMR cluster took a while.

00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:26.000
Like you actually had to know how to do this thing, right?

00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:28.000
To get it working.

00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:31.000
And then to set up a table, like a permanent table,

00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:32.000
you had to do an S3 bucket.

00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:35.000
And then there's a lot of work that you have to do.

00:17:35.000 --> 00:17:39.000
But with Databricks, everything is so easy to do.

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:41.000
I feel like as a data scientist,

00:17:41.000 --> 00:17:44.000
it gives you that,

00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:48.000
those almost like superpowers at your fingertips

00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:50.000
where you can have a Spark cluster

00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:53.000
and a volume running so you can have pins

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:56.000
and a table ready for you to have data in.

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:58.000
Within like, you know, half an hour,

00:17:58.000 --> 00:17:59.000
you have everything set up

00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:01.000
without it being too complicated.

00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:03.000
Connect it to your RStudio, to Positron, to your notebook

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:07.000
and get going and analyze large amounts of data.

00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:08.000
This is kind of like the dream

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:11.000
that we've had for years happening now

