00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:25.000
One specific about pins was,

00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:29.000
do pins live outside version control like Git?

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:31.000
Yeah, it does live outside of it.

00:19:31.000 --> 00:19:33.000
And I think there are two different concepts.

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:38.000
Git is to track changes to your code,

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:40.000
to the implementation code.

00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:42.000
The version that you have in pins

00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:45.000
is to track differences in the data itself.

00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:48.000
That's the main thing that you have to keep in mind.

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:50.000
And I would say,

00:19:50.000 --> 00:19:52.000
if you think about in terms of,

00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:55.000
okay, I want to use this specific version of pins

00:19:56.000 --> 00:19:57.000
in your code.

00:19:57.000 --> 00:20:00.000
If you say, okay, I used to use this version,

00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:01.000
I'm going to use this version.

00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:03.000
That's what you track in Git, right?

00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:05.000
The versioning that is in pins.

00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:08.000
So yeah, there are two different things in my opinion.

